  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Human Resource Executive",
  "description": "<p>We are looking for a <strong>Human Resource Executive </strong>to join our growing team!<br /></p><p><u><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></u><br /><br /><strong>HR Operations & Administration</strong></p><ul><li>Handle end-to-end HR functions including recruitment coordination, onboarding, and offboarding.</li><li>Maintain and update employee records, contracts, and personal files.</li><li>Implement HR policies and SOPs in line with MOM regulations.</li></ul><p><strong>Payroll & Compensation</strong></p><ul><li>Prepare monthly payroll and ensure accuracy and timeliness.</li><li>Manage employee claims, leave, and attendance records through the HR system.</li><li>Work with accounts to ensure CPF and statutory contributions are in order.</li></ul><p><strong>Employee Relations & Engagement</strong></p><ul><li>Serve as the first point of contact for HR-related queries from staff.</li><li>Support staff welfare, engagement, and team-building initiatives.</li><li>Handle employee grievances or disciplinary matters with tact and confidentiality.</li></ul><p><strong>Franchise Growth Support</strong></p><ul><li>Assist in building scalable HR frameworks and processes as the business grows.</li></ul><ul><li>Support HR matters related to future franchise outlets including manpower planning and recruitment coordination</li></ul><p><u><strong>Requirements</strong></u></p><ul><li>Diploma or Degree in Human Resource Management, Business Administration, or related discipline.</li><li>At least 5 years of relevant working experience in F&B</li><li>Good understanding of local employment laws, regulations, and HR best practices.</li><li>Hands-on experience with HRIS system (Infotech Software) and MS Office applications.</li><li>Strong interpersonal and communication skills.</li><li>Meticulous and proactive</li><li>Takes initiative to complete the task assigned</li><li>Able to work independently with minimum amount of supervision</li></ul>",
